arn.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the provisioned S3 bucket. Will be of format arn:aws:s3:::bucketname

bucket_domain_name.description: The bucket domain name. Will be of format bucketname.s3.amazonaws.com

hosted_zone_id.description: The Route 53 Hosted Zone ID for this bucket's region.

id.description: The globally unique identifier for the provisioned S3 bucket.

region.description: The AWS region the provisioned S3 bucket resides in

website_domain.description: The domain of the static S3 website endpoint, if static_hosting was enabled. If not, this will be an empty string. This is used to create Route 53 alias records.

website_endpoint.description: The static S3 website endpoint, if static_hosting was enabled. If not, this will be an empty string.

acl.description: The Access Control List that will be placed on the bucket. Acceptable Values are: 'private', 'public-read', 'public-read-write', 'aws-exec-read', 'authenticated-read', 'bucket-owner-read', 'bucket-owner-full-control', or 'log-delivery-write'

bucket.description: The base name that will be given to the S3 bucket. This base name can be made unique by specifing values for bucket_prefix, bucket_suffix, or both.

bucket_prefix.description: A prefix list that will be added to the start of the bucket name. For example if bucket_prefix=['test'], then the bucket will be named 'test-${bucket}'. This module will also look for the keywords 'region_prefix' and 'account_prefix' and will substitute the current region, or account_id within the module as in the example: bucket_prefix=['test', 'region_prefix', 'account_prefix'], resulting in the bucket 'test-us-east-1-1234567890101-${bucket}'. If left blank no prefix will be added.

bucket_suffix.description: A suffix list that will be added to the end of the bucket name. For example if bucket_suffix=['test'], then the bucket will be named '${bucket}-test'. This module will also look for the keywords 'region_suffix' and 'account_suffix' and will substitute the current region, or account_id within the module as in the example: bucket_suffix=['region_suffix', 'account_suffix', 'test'], resulting in the bucket name '${bucket}-us-east-1-1234567890101-test'. If left blank no suffix will be added.

cors_rule.description: Cross Origin Resource Sharing ruleset to apply to the bucket

custom_policy.description: A bucket policy in the form of a data iam_policy_document. Use %BUCKET% for bucket name. This policy will be added to the read_access/write_access policy.

disable_rw_policy.description: Setting this optional flag to true will disable any automatically generated policies and will ONLY use the custom_policy. The read_access and write_access vars will be ignored.

encryption.description: Flag to enable bucket object encryption.

error_document.description: Value of the error file served by the static hosting bucket server if static hosting is enabled.

index_document.description: Value of the index file served by the static hosting bucket server if static hosting is enabled.

kms_master_key_id.description: The key that will be used to encrypt objects within the new bucket. If the default value of AES256 is unchanged, S3 will encrypt objects with the default KMS key. If a KMS CMK ARN is provided, then S3 will encrypt objects with the specified KMS key instead.

logging_bucket.description: The base name of an S3 bucket designated as the log bucket for the provisioned s3 buckets access logs

mfa_delete.description: Flag to enable the requirement of MFA in order to delete a bucket, object, or disable object versioning.

read_access.description: List of users/roles that will be granted permissions to LIST, DESCRIBE, and GET objects from the provisioned S3 bucket.

region.description: The AWS region where the S3 bucket will be provisioned.

static_hosting.description: Flag that can be set to turn on static hosting within a bucket.

tags.description: Specify any tags that should be added to the S3 bucket being provisioned.

versioning.description: Flag to enable bucket object versioning.

write_access.description: List of users/roles that will be granted permissions to PUT, and DELETE objects to/from the provisioned S3 bucket.
